feat(security): API-level rate limiting on /api/*

- Hand-rolled per-IP fixed-window limiter (no new dep; mirrors the
  PermissionManager.checkRateLimit idiom), registered after the source-IP
  allowlist gate and in front of express.json + the bearer gate, so
  unauthenticated token-guessing is also capped.
- Exempts loopback + BOOKCLAW_ALLOWED_IPS members (reuses isIpAllowed), so
  localhost self-calls and trusted IPs are never throttled.
- Auth-aware buckets keyed req.ip + |auth/|anon (independent counters); a new
  shared extractToken(req) helper drives both the rate-limit and bearer gates so
  "is authenticated" can't drift. Auth-disabled => open gate => generous bucket.
- On exceed: 429 + Retry-After + audit rate_limited event.
- Env-configurable, posture logged at startup: BOOKCLAW_RATELIMIT_UNAUTH (30),
  BOOKCLAW_RATELIMIT_AUTH (360 = 6/sec), BOOKCLAW_RATELIMIT_WINDOW_MS (60000);
  a limit of 0 disables that bucket.
- Tests: smoke-test Phase 5 (7 checks, TDD) drives non-loopback IPs via XFF
  under trust-proxy — anon 429 past strict limit w/ Retry-After, authed sails
  past strict and 429s past generous (independent buckets), loopback exempt.
- tsc clean; npm test green (34 unit + API + smoke). Moved the item from
  docs/TODO.md to docs/COMPLETED.md.

Note: docs/NERDY-NOVELIST-WORKFLOW.md + its TODO entry are a separate, still-
